BRAZIL DAYBOOK: Petrobras Earnings, Central Bank Event in Rio

-- B y   H e l d e r   M a r i n h o
-- 
2011-05-13T03:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-13/brazil-daybook-petrobras-earnings-central-bank-event-in-rio.html
Petroleo Brasileiro SA, the world’s
fourth-largest oil company by market value, is expected to
report today a first-quarter profit of 9.74 billion reais ($6.01
billion), according to the average estimate of seven analysts
surveyed by Bloomberg. The state-controlled oil producer posted
net income of 7.73 billion for the period a  year earlier. Chief
Financial Officer Almir Barbassa will discuss the company’s
results in a press conference in  Rio de Janeiro  after the
markets close.  GOVERNMENT:
*President  Dilma Rousseff  has internal dispatches starting at
10:00 a.m.
*Finance Minister  Guido Mantega  meets with the board of
Petrobras at 9:30 a.m. in Sao Paulo. Mantega has internal
meetings at Banco do Brasil in the afternoon, also in Sao Paulo
*Central bank president Alexandre Tombini has internal meetings
in Brasilia  WHAT TO WATCH:
*President Dilma Rousseff’s administration is considering cuts
to taxes on electricity and fuel as it seeks to rein in consumer
prices, a person familiar with the discussions said.
*The central bank’s Economic Policy Director Carlos
Hamilton de Araújo speaks at the bank’s annual seminar on
inflation target, in Rio de Janeiro at 12:40 p.m.
*ETH Bioenergia’s Chief Executive Officer Jose Carlos Grubisich
and directors of  Brazil ’s sugar and ethanol association, known
as Unica, speak at a journalists workshop in the state of Goias.
*Executives of BRF  Brasil Foods  speak to reporters in Sao Paulo
about the company’s first-quarter results, at 5:30 p.m.
*Morgan Stanley plans to sell four-year real-denominated debt
linked to Brazilian inflation as soon as this week, according to
a person familiar with the transaction.  EARNINGS:
*Light (LIGT3 BZ), bef. mkt.
*Petrobras (PETR3 BZ), aft. mkt
*Brasil Foods (BRFS3 BZ), aft. mkt
*Cesp (CESP6 BZ), aft. mkt  EQUITIES:
*Cemig (CMIG4 BS) said Parati bought 54% Redentor for 403.4
million reais
*BM&FBovespa (BVMF3 BS) posts first-quarter profit of 384.2
million reais
*Cyrela (CYRE3 BZ) to sell 550 million reais in local bonds
*MRV Engenharia (MRVE3 BS) posts first-quarter profit of 152.6
million reais  MARKETS
*The Bovespa index rose 0.4 percent to 64,003.16. *The real rose
0.1 percent to 1.6198 per dollar.  To contact the reporter on this story:
